theorem
Lm7: (for n holds (( 1 - ( 1 / ( n + 2 ) ) ) = ( ( n + 1 ) / ( n + 2 ) ) & ( 1 / ( ( n + 1 ) ! ) ) = ( ( n + 2 ) / ( ( ( n + 1 ) ! ) * ( n + 2 ) ) )))
proof
let n;
n >= ( 0 ) by NAT_1:2;
then ( n + 1 ) > ( 0 ) by NAT_1:13;
then A1: ( ( n + 1 ) + 1 ) > ( 0 ) by NAT_1:13;
then A2: ( 1 / ( ( n + 1 ) ! ) ) = ( ( 1 * ( n + 2 ) ) / ( ( ( n + 1 ) ! ) * ( n + 2 ) ) ) by XCMPLX_1:91;
( ( n + 1 ) / ( n + 2 ) ) = ( ( ( n + 2 ) - 1 ) / ( n + 2 ) )
.= ( ( ( n + 2 ) / ( n + 2 ) ) - ( 1 / ( n + 2 ) ) ) by XCMPLX_1:120
.= ( 1 - ( 1 / ( n + 2 ) ) ) by A1,XCMPLX_1:60;
hence thesis by A2;
end;
